cern.extjfx.chart.data

Class ArrayData<X extends Number,Y extends Number>

  • java.lang.Object
    • cern.extjfx.chart.data.ArrayData<X,Y>
  • Type Parameters:
    X - type of X values
    Y - type of Y values
    All Implemented Interfaces:
    ChartData<X,Y>, Observable

    public class ArrayData<X extends Number,Y extends Number>
extends Object
implements ChartData<X,Y>
    Immutable holder of chart data represented by two primitive arrays (X and Y). Instances of the class can be created using dedicated builder() class that allows specifying X and Y coordinates as on the following example: 
     
 long[] xValues = ...;
 float[] yValues = ...;
 ArrayData<Number, Number> arrayData = ArrayData.builder().x(xValues).y(yValues).build();
 //Convert to ObservableList that can be given directly to Chart Series
 ObservableList<Data<Number, Number>> data = arrayData.toObservableList();
    If both arrays are of the same type one of the of(..) methods can be used instead e.g.: 
     
 double[] xValues = ...;
 double[] yValues = ...;
 ObservableList<Data<Number, Number>> data = ArrayData.of(xValues, yValues).toObservableList();
 
 Series<Number, Number> series = ...;
 series.setData(data);
